Inv.CommonName: Morgan Stanley Institutional US Real Estate Fund (A)

Obj.ObjectiveStatement: The Fund seeks to provide above average current income and long-term capital appreciation. The Fund normally invests primarily in equity securities of companies in the U.S. real estate industry. The adviser seeks a combination of above-average current income and long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in equity securities of companies in the U.S. real estate industry, including REITs. The Fund focuses on REITs as well as real estate operating companies (REOCs) that invest in a variety of property types and regions. It is non-diversified.

Inv.CommonName: VY American Century Small-Mid Cap Value Fund (S)

Obj.ObjectiveStatement: The Fund seeks long-term capital growth; income is a secondary objective. The Fund invests primarily in equity securities of small- and mid-capitalization companies which are defined as those with a market capitalization no larger than that of the largest company in the S&P SmallCap 600 Index or the Russell 2000 Index and mid-capitalization companies to include those whose market capitalization at the time of purchase within the capitalization range of the Russell 3000 Index, excluding the largest 100 such companies.
